.TH ANNOSCR 1 "2026" "Annoscr" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
annoscr \- annotate screenshots
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B annoscr
[\fIOPTION\fR...] [\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Annoscr
is a lightweight screenshot annotation tool for GNOME. Add arrows, text,
shapes, highlighter strokes, and numbered stamps to an image, rotate or resize
it, then export to PNG or JPEG or copy it to the clipboard.
.PP
With no arguments it opens an empty window. \fIFILE\fR may be an image (PNG,
JPEG, and so on) or a saved \fB.annoscr\fR annotation file; it opens as the
starting canvas. This is also how the desktop "Open With" entry launches the
program.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-new
Start with a blank canvas (640x480 by default) instead of an empty window.
.TP
.BI \-\-width " PIXELS"
Blank-canvas width in pixels (default 640, range 1\-8192). Requires \fB\-\-new\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-height " PIXELS"
Blank-canvas height in pixels (default 480, range 1\-8192). Requires \fB\-\-new\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-screenshot
Capture a screenshot through the desktop portal on startup, replacing the
canvas. \fB\-\-new\fR has no effect when combined with this.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the built-in help and exit. Standard GTK options (such as
.BR \-\-display )
are also accepted.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/annoscr/settings.json
User preferences (color scheme, default save folder and format, remembered
tool styles, and the curated text-font list).
.SH SEE ALSO
Project homepage: <https://github.com/mdmower/annoscr>
